  "prompt": "What does it feel like to overhear somebody talk behind your back?",
  "response": "Overhearing someone talk behind your back can evoke a variety of emotions, often leading to feelings of betrayal, hurt, or anger. You might feel vulnerable or exposed, especially if the conversation involved negative comments or gossip. It can also trigger self-doubt, making you question your worth or relationships. \n\nOn the other hand, some might feel a sense of curiosity, wanting to understand the context or content of the discussion. It can also lead to a stronger resolve to confront the individuals involved or to distance oneself from them. Overall, the experience can be quite unsettling and can impact both your emotional state and your relationships with others.",
